# lint-css.allowlist — snapshot of PRE-EXISTING, accepted CSS parse
# messages in the merged tree at gate-install time. Each non-comment,
# non-blank line is a distinctive SUBSTRING of an accepted GTK
# CssProvider message; any message containing one of these substrings
# is treated as accepted (not a failure). This file is meant to SHRINK
# over time as each entry is resolved.
#
# Format: one substring per line. Keep it specific enough not to mask
# net-new errors.

# 2026-06-03 — greeter.css deliberately @import's the INSTALLED runtime
# theme path (file:///usr/share/mde/theme/tokens.css), which only exists
# after `make install` / RPM install (DM-3). At lint time that file is
# absent, so GTK reports an import-failure — a path-resolution artifact,
# not a CSS-syntax defect. Accepted pre-existing condition.
/usr/share/mde/theme/tokens.css
